ng... values) {\\n            return prefix + \\\":\\\" + String.join(\\\",\\\", values);\\n        }\\n    }\\n\\n    public interface LabelProvider {\\n        String label(String value);\\n    }\\n\\n    private static final class InterfaceImplementation implements LabelProvider {\\n        @Override\\n        public String label(String value) {\\n            return \\\"label:\\\" + value;\\n        }\\n    }\\n\\n    public static class PublicSuperclass {\\n        public String format(String value) {\\n            return \\\"format:\\\" + value;\\n        }\\n    }\\n\\n    private static final class SuperclassImplementation extends PublicSuperclass {\\n    }\\n\\n    public static class PublicConstructorSuperclass {\\n        public PublicConstructorSuperclass(String value) {\\n        }\\n    }\\n\\n    private static final class ConstructorImplementation extends PublicConstructorSuperclass {\\n        private ConstructorImplementation(String value) {\\n            super(value);\\n        }\\n    }\\n}\\n\",\"exit_code\":0,\"status\":\"completed\"}}\n{\"type\":\"item.completed\",\"item\":{\"id\":\"item_14\",\"type\":\"agent_message\",\"text\":\"`reachability-metadata.json` is currently empty, so this looks like the first real coverage being added for `4.0.0`. I’m checking how similar metadata in this repo handles `condition` for libraries whose Maven group and Java package differ, so the new entry stays consistent.\"}}\n{\"type\":\"item.started\",\"item\":{\"id\":\"item_15\",\"type\":\"command_execution\",\"command\":\"/usr/bin/bash -lc \\\"sed -n '1,220p' metadata/jakarta.el/jakarta.el-api/3.0.2/reachability-metadata.json\\\"\",\"aggregated_output\":\"\",\"exit_code\":null,\"status\":\"in_progress\"}}\n{\"type\":\"item.completed\",\"item\":{\"id\":\"item_15\",\"type\":\"command_execution\",\"command\":\"/usr/bin/bash -lc \\\"sed -n '1,220p' metadata/jakarta.el/jakarta.el-api/3.0.2/reachability-metadata.json\\\"\",\"aggregated_output\":\"{\\n  \\\"reflection\